Surprised this only has 49 views in almost 4 years, I had the same issue. The following was enough to keep my text centered in the textview for multiple lines, but not one line, just like in your image:

    flavorTextView.setGravity(Gravity.CENTER_VERTICAL|Gravity.CENTER_HORIZONTAL);
    flavortextParams = new FrameLayout.LayoutParams(ViewGroup.LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT, ViewGroup.LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT);
    flavortextParams.topMargin = 0;
    flavorTextView.setLayoutParams(flavortextParams)

To get centered text for just one line I had to add:

    flavortextParams.gravity = Gravity.CENTER_HORIZONTAL;

This is because multiple lines of text automatically sets the textview width to the screenwidth, so the textview (and the wrapped text) is automatically centered. This isn&#39;t the case with just one line of text unless it happens to extend to the width of the screen.

